comments.content:
@Kalaivanan:

We need additional information to do a proper bug triage.
Would you please provide the following information:

* Which versions did you use? Depending on your package manager you can 
  use:
    $ dpkg -l | grep nova
    or:
    $ rpm -ql | grep nova

  If you installed it from git you can use:
    $ cd /opt/stack/nova && git log -1
  
  Please give the versions of **both** nodes.

After you provided this information, please set this bug status back
to "New".
comments.author: https://api.launchpad.net/1.0/~mzoeller

comments.content: I'm fairly certain that your new compute node is running another (older) version of nova, which is why you're getting this error. The error would be generated from a very outdated version, so please make sure that your new compute node is running the same version as the rest of your deployment.
comments.author: https://api.launchpad.net/1.0/~danms

comments.content: [Expired for OpenStack Compute (nova) because there has been no activity for 60 days.]
